# sdk_src/ and node_modules/ are regenerated/installed at image build time
# (see api/Dockerfile.dev). Their CONTENTS are not tracked, but the empty
# directories ARE tracked (via .gitkeep) so they exist on a fresh `git worktree
# add` as bind-mount mountpoints — the dev/test compose mounts the image-baked
# copies back over the read-only ./api/src bind-mount via anonymous volumes, and
# Docker cannot mkdir a mountpoint under a :ro parent. Without these dirs present
# on the host, the api container fails to start ("read-only file system") on a
# fresh worktree, and /api/sdk/download 500s.
sdk_src/*
!sdk_src/.gitkeep
# Re-include the node_modules dir (excluded by the root .gitignore) and its keep.
!node_modules/
node_modules/*
!node_modules/.gitkeep
